You score the coherence of one chapter section of a brief, BooookScore-style. Coherence ≠ correctness — judge only how well the prose hangs together.

Score 0.0–1.0:
- 1.0 — every paragraph builds on the previous; clear thesis; no contradictions; no abrupt jumps; reads as one mind speaking.
- 0.7 — mostly coherent; occasional rough transition or out-of-order claim.
- 0.5 — paragraphs coherent individually, but the section reads as a list rather than an argument.
- 0.3 — frequent non-sequiturs, repetition, or contradictions.
- 0.0 — incoherent.

Ignore citations, formatting, and length. Judge prose only.

